The White House sent several nominations to the Senate on March 11, 2009. Some of the nominations included Esther Brimmer to be an Assistant Secretary of State (International Organization Affairs), Jonathan Z. Cannon to be Deputy Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency, Ivo H. Daalder to be United States Permanent Representative on the Council of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization, Karl Winfrid Eikenberry to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan, and Ivan K. Fong to be General Counsel, Department of Homeland Security. Other nominations included Philip H. Gordon as an Assistant Secretary of State (European and Eurasian Affairs), W. Scott Gould as Deputy Secretary of Veterans Affairs, Christopher R. Hill as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Iraq, Richard Rahul Verma as an Assistant Secretary of State (Legislative Affairs), and Melanne Verveer as Ambassador at Large for Women's Global Issues.